↓
Auto-charge: /pattern nextjs
↓
Pattern fourni
```

**Résultat (dans le skill) :**

```markdown
# skills/patterns/nextjs/nextjs-patterns.skill

> **Triggers:** "server action", "use server", "revalidateTag"

## Server Action Pattern
'use server'

import { z } from 'zod'
import { revalidateTag } from 'next/cache'

const schema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1),
})

export async function createPost(formData: FormData) {
  const data = schema.parse({
    title: formData.get('title'),
  })

  const post = await db.post.create({ data })

  revalidateTag('posts')

  return post
}
```

**Triggers mutuellement exclusifs :**
- "server action", "use server" → nextjs pattern
- "Axum handler", "sqlx" → rust pattern
- "DTO validation", "JWT guard" → nestjs pattern

**Quality Gates :**
- [ ] Pattern exécutable
- [ ] Triggers exclusifs
- [ ] Code complet
- [ ] Portable entre projets

